item.title: Aussies’ post-lockdown pokies binge
item.description: Australians have sunk hundreds of millions of dollars into poker machines since emerging from COVID-19 lockdowns, prompting renewed calls for licensed premises to do more to reduce rates of addiction.

item.title: Suburbs hit hardest by JobSeeker cuts
item.description: Residents in Adelaide’s northern suburbs are set to lose $300 a fortnight under changes to the federal government’s coronavirus support.

item.title: Horror attack captured on swell camera
Suburbs hardest hit by JobSeeker
item.description: Residents in Melbourne’s outer suburbs are set to lose $300 a fortnight under changes to the Federal Government’s coronavirus support.

item.title: Aussies taking relatives out of aged care
item.description: More Australians are taking their elderly relatives out of aged-care facilities as the COVID-19 pandemic continues to expose cracks in the troubled sector, new data shows.

item.title: Man caught with ‘sinister’ material to make explosives
item.description: An Adelaide man found with volatile substances and instructions on how to make explosives could be freed from jail in less than 3 months.

item.title: WA nurse gets virus in Victoria
item.description: A WA nurse who was among a group of volunteers sent to help Victoria’s response to the pandemic has contracted COVID-19, forcing the entire group to go into isolation.

item.title: Judge puts foot down in CBD stabber case
item.description: A Sydney magistrate says delays in the case of a man who allegedly stabbed a young woman to death before terrorising Sydney’s CBD last year have dragged on long enough.

item.title: ‘I just wanted it to be over’
item.description: A woman who claims an alleged dating app rapist coerced her into giving him oral sex has told a court she didn’t immediately call police because she “just wanted it to be over”.
